&lt;p&gt;Perry Ellis International, Inc. represents a diverse portfolio of lifestyle apparel brands. The Company, through its wholly owned subsidiaries owns and licenses nationally and with a brand portfolio of over 40 Brands domestically and internationally recognized brands including: Perry Ellis®, Original Penguin® by Munsingwear®, Laundry by Shelli Segal®, Rafaella®, Cubavera®, Ben Hogan®, Savane®, Grand Slam®, John Henry®, Manhattan®, Axist® and Farah®. The Company enhances its roster of brands by licensing trademarks from third parties, including: Nike®&amp;nbsp; for swimwear, and Callaway®, PGA TOUR®, and Jack Nicklaus® for golf apparel.&lt;/p&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;SUMMARY:&amp;nbsp;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;br&gt;Perry Ellis is seeking an Assistant Men&#39;s Designer to join the New York Design team in the&amp;nbsp;woven shirt category. The Assistant Men&#39;s Designer will be responsible for assisting all parts of&amp;nbsp;the design process, including preparation of technical packages and seasonal presentation&amp;nbsp;boards, understanding of PDM process, email correspondence, etc.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;RESPONSIBILITIES:&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Assist recoloring prints and patterns.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Assist with basic specification of product.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Make revisions to sketches and design packages as needed.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Market and trend research.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Responsible for maintaining design folders for reference.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Responsible for 3D rendering.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Responsible for creating inspiration boards, mini boards for sales tools, etc.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;strong&gt;SKILLS:&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Basic computer knowledge.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Ability to learn how to design through new/advanced technology (Gemini, Fermat,&lt;br&gt;Browzwear).&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Good understanding of color and print.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Experience in design or product development in the Men&#39;s Contemporary Market&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Basic knowledge of product and fabric.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Basic knowledge and understanding of garment construction.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&amp;nbsp;Basic knowledge of design and color.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Ability to perform basic flat sketches.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Good organizational and communication skills.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;br&gt;R&lt;strong&gt;EQUIREMENTS:&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;College degree in Fashion Design or equivalent experience.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;One year design experience (may include summer jobs, internships, etc.)&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Expertise in Adobe Illustrator&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Salary offered will be at the discretion of the Company and based on a candidate’s qualifications. &amp;nbsp;For this position, the base salary will be between $25.00 - $32.00 hourly.&amp;nbsp; Other benefits associated with the position for eligible associates are listed below.&lt;/p&gt;&lt;div class=&quot;content-conclusion&quot;&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-size: 14pt;&quot;&gt;&lt;strong&gt;What’s In It For You? &lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
