&lt;div class=&quot;content-intro&quot;&gt;&lt;h3&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Company Overview&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/h3&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Perry Ellis International, Inc. represents a diverse portfolio of lifestyle apparel brands. The Company, through its wholly owned subsidiaries owns and licenses nationally and with a brand portfolio of over 40 Brands domestically and internationally recognized brands including: Perry Ellis®, Original Penguin® by Munsingwear®, Laundry by Shelli Segal®, Rafaella®, Cubavera®, Ben Hogan®, Savane®, Grand Slam®, John Henry®, Manhattan®, Axist® and Farah®. The Company enhances its roster of brands by licensing trademarks from third parties, including: Nike®&amp;nbsp; for swimwear, and Callaway®, PGA TOUR®, and Jack Nicklaus® for golf apparel.&lt;/p&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;p&gt;As the Assistant Designer for Callaway Men’s, you will manage the administrative and follow-up aspects of the product design process, ensuring timely and accurate execution of the line from initial concept to final production handoff. You will actively support the design team&#39;s creative vision by preparing technical sketches, managing component approvals, and executing technical fitting directives. The ideal candidate will blend a passion for premium men&#39;s athletic/lifestyle apparel with an eagerness to leverage cutting-edge design technology.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;h3&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Key Responsibilities&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/h3&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Design &amp;amp; Conceptual Development: Actively participate in the creative process for Callaway Men’s. Provide innovative recommendations regarding seasonal themes, line edits, fabrication, and new concepts that align with market trends and the brand’s business strategy.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Technical Sketching &amp;amp; Specification: Own the precise design details of products. Responsible for preparing, updating, and maintaining accurate technical sketches (utilizing Adobe Illustrator) and detailed specifications.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Fittings &amp;amp; Execution: Lead or actively participate in technical design fittings, clearly defining and communicating go-forward directives to ensure fit updates are executed accurately and on time.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Design Package Completion: Ensure the product design package is complete, accurate, and handed off on schedule to the Product Development team, Technical Design department, and vendors for the creation of prototypes and salesmen samples.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Approval &amp;amp; Production Readiness: Monitor and manage the approval process for material and color components, including lab-dips, knit-downs, strike-offs, and handlooms. Responsible for the final approval of sales samples to ensure the garment is fully production-ready.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Product Consistency: Assist in ensuring that the product design is cohesive, trend-relevant, and aligned with Callaway’s established performance and lifestyle aesthetic.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
