&lt;div class=&quot;content-intro&quot;&gt;&lt;h3&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Company Overview&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/h3&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Perry Ellis International, Inc. represents a diverse portfolio of lifestyle apparel brands. The Company, through its wholly owned subsidiaries owns and licenses nationally and with a brand portfolio of over 40 Brands domestically and internationally recognized brands including: Perry Ellis®, Original Penguin® by Munsingwear®, Laundry by Shelli Segal®, Rafaella®, Cubavera®, Ben Hogan®, Savane®, Grand Slam®, John Henry®, Manhattan®, Axist® and Farah®. The Company enhances its roster of brands by licensing trademarks from third parties, including: Nike®&amp;nbsp; for swimwear, and Callaway®, PGA TOUR®, and Jack Nicklaus® for golf apparel.&lt;/p&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Position Summary:&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;As the Human Resources Manager, you would be responsible for serving as the primary human resources contact for all employees based in our New York office. Reporting directly to the Chief Human Resources Officer (CHRO), you will be responsible for managing employee relations, performance management, training, policy implementation, and local compliance. You will act as a strategic partner to local management, helping to foster a positive, productive, and compliant work environment.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;h3&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Key Responsibilities:&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/h3&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Employee Relations:&lt;/strong&gt; Manage and resolve complex employee relations issues, conducting effective, thorough, and objective investigations. Provide guidance and coaching to managers and employees on performance improvement, conflict resolution, and disciplinary actions.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Performance Management&lt;/strong&gt;: Support and administer the company&#39;s performance review process, working with managers to ensure timely and effective feedback, goal setting, and development planning.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Policy &amp;amp; Compliance:&lt;/strong&gt; Interpret and ensure consistent application of all company policies and procedures. Stay current on federal, state (New York and New Jersey), and local employment law to ensure legal compliance and mitigate risk.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Recruitment &amp;amp; Onboarding:&lt;/strong&gt; Partner with the Corporate Talent Acquisition team to support local recruitment needs. Oversee the new hire onboarding process for New York employees to ensure a smooth and engaging transition.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Training &amp;amp; Development:&lt;/strong&gt; Identify training needs and develop or facilitate local employee development programs, including manager training and mandatory compliance courses.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;HR Administration:&lt;/strong&gt; Manage day-to-day HR administrative tasks for the local office, including reporting, data integrity, and maintaining employee records.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;h3&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Qualifications:&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/h3&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Experience: &lt;/strong&gt;5+ years of progressive HR experience, preferably as an HR Manager or Senior HR Generalist, operating in a standalone capacity or with minimal local HR support.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Education: &lt;/strong&gt;Bachelor&#39;s degree in Human Resources, Business Administration, or a related field. HR certification (SHRM-CP/SCP or PHR/SPHR) is highly desirable.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Legal Knowledge: &lt;/strong&gt;Expert knowledge of local, state, and federal employment laws, with specific emphasis on New York (NY) and New Jersey (NJ) labor law and compliance requirements.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Skills: &lt;/strong&gt;Demonstrated ability to manage complex employee relations issues, excellent judgment, and strong analytical problem-solving skills.&lt;/p&gt;
