&lt;p&gt;Position Summary:&lt;br&gt;As the Buyer for Perry Ellis Sportswear, this person will be responsible for driving the seasonal product lifecycle, business strategy, and open-to-buy management for a large-scale, high-volume category based out of our Corporate Office in Miami, FL. Operating within the Buying department and reporting directly to the Senior Director of Omnichannel Buying, you will oversee a complex, high-caliber business scope encompassing 10 distinct product departments, managing a matrixed inventory architecture of 350 go-forward SCIs (Style-Colors) distributed across Fashion, Core, and Seasonal color capsules.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The ideal candidate must possess deep expertise in menswear buying alongside a proven track record of architecting, managing, and scaling heavy, complex assortments to the caliber of Perry Ellis. You will combine strong retail math proficiency with apparel intuition to orchestrate a high-velocity buying operation that includes developing and introducing roughly 150 new styles every single quarter. You will act as a central collaborative hub between Sales, Planning, Sourcing, and Design to construct optimized, high-velocity product assortments that safeguard margin goals and consistently deliver brand success.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Key Responsibilities:&lt;br&gt;High-Caliber Assortment Architecture: Drive the end-to-end buying strategy across 10 specialized sportswear departments. Masterfully engineer large-scale seasonal matrices to manage 350 baseline SCIs, balancing the life-cycle economics of high-velocity core lines with the injection of roughly 150 new high-impact fashion styles per quarter.&lt;br&gt;Menswear Strategy Exploration: Apply deep industry knowledge of menswear fits, fabrications, seasonal trends, and category performance to curate product lines that resonate with the Perry Ellis consumer while maintaining brand DNA.&lt;br&gt;Financial Strategy, Margin Delivery &amp;amp; Pricing: Execute detailed quarterly and seasonal buy plans designed to meet corporate financial targets, OTB thresholds, and gross margin requirements. Manage strategic pricing structures and deliver deep-dive product analysis including sell-through performance, best-seller tracking, and historical margin contribution to maximize ROI.&lt;br&gt;Cross-Functional Sourcing &amp;amp; Workflow Execution: Partner with Sourcing, Design, Marketing, Store/ECOM Teams, Allocation, and Planning teams to manage seasonal timelines, tracking critical production components from technical design sketch approvals through sample buy confirmations.&lt;br&gt;Vendor &amp;amp; Lifecycle Management: Systematically manage Jesta and PLM purchasing systems to accurately validate order entries, manage SKU counts, adjust for delivery changes, and prevent inventory discrepancies. Actively maintain strategic vendor relationships to ensure all Perry Ellis business needs are consistently met through intentional assortment selection, on-time delivery tracking, and preferred costing negotiations.&lt;br&gt;Market-Facing Partnerships: Attend seasonal market weeks and key retail vendor appointments to present unified collection visions and

&lt;div class=&quot;content-intro&quot;&gt;&lt;h3&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Company Overview&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/h3&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Perry Ellis International, Inc. represents a diverse portfolio of lifestyle apparel brands. The Company, through its wholly owned subsidiaries owns and licenses nationally and with a brand portfolio of over 40 Brands domestically and internationally recognized brands including: Perry Ellis®, Original Penguin® by Munsingwear®, Laundry by Shelli Segal®, Rafaella®, Cubavera®, Ben Hogan®, Savane®, Grand Slam®, John Henry®, Manhattan®, Axist® and Farah®. The Company enhances its roster of brands by licensing trademarks from third parties, including: Nike®&amp;nbsp; for swimwear, and Callaway®, PGA TOUR®, and Jack Nicklaus® for golf apparel.&lt;/p&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Position Overview:&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;As the Senior Merchandiser, you will be responsible for leading the product lifecycle, from initial concept through final sales execution. This includes managing the development calendar, executing merchandising and digital strategies, ensuring profitability through pricing and margin management, and maintaining a consistent brand image. You will serve as the central hub, collaborating with design, sales, planning, sourcing, and management to ensure a unified vision and drive market success.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Responsibilities:&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Strategy &amp;amp; Profitability: Execute seasonal line plans and merchandising strategies to build profitable assortments that meet internal margin goals. Manage national marketing strategies to finalize pricing and margins in collaboration with Sales, Planning, Sourcing, and Management.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Product Development Management: Oversee and maintain the design calendar and development process to ensure timely completion of all products. Interface with all functional areas of the business (design, sales, sourcing, marketing) to maintain a common vision for the brand.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Digital &amp;amp; Selling Tools: Drive the implementation and execution of digital merchandising strategies utilizing tools like 3D and NuOrder. Strategically develop compelling selling tools to enhance all digital presentations to customers.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Leadership &amp;amp; Collaboration: Collaborate closely with the Design Director to monitor assortments and maintain a consistent brand image. Attend market appointments with accounts to present brand strategy and designs. Selects, trains, motivates, and evaluates direct reports, encouraging proper growth and development of Assistant/Associate Merchandisers.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Financial Oversight: Attend market appointments with accounts to present brand strategy and designs. Responsible for creating and adhering to annual budgets for samples and travel.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Qualifications:&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Experience: 5-7 years of professional merchandising experience is required.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Education: A Bachelor&#39;s Degree in Business or Merchandising (or equivalent experience from a Design school) is required, though more years of professional experience can compensate.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Analytical Skills: Proficiency in Retail Math, best seller analysis, and competitive landscape analysis.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Core Knowledge: Deep knowledge of the product development process and brand management.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Technical Skills: Proficient in MS Office and Google applications. Must be highly skilled in Excel/Google Sheets, including the ability to manipulate data.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Project Management: Proven ability to manage complex, multi-stage projects under tight deadlines, demonstrating superior organizational and time management skills.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;
